akas from release info: Bubble Guppies - Un tuffo nel blu e impari di più Italy

1.title: The Glitter Games!
1.plot: Learn all about manners with the Guppies, as Molly helps aspiring princess Demanda get polite in time for the Glitter Games! Will they become true princesses together?

2.title: Costume Boxing!
2.plot: At the height of Fashion Week in Bubbletucky, Molly performs in the quick-change dress-up match. Her skills land her on the cover of Dress-Up!, the hottest fashion mag in town!

3.title: The New Doghouse!
3.plot: When an accident destroys Bubble Puppy's doghouse, the Guppies team up with the entire neighborhood to build Bubble Puppy's dream home - the most tricked out doghouse Bubbletucky has ever seen!

4.title: Guppy Movers!
4.plot: When their friend's moving day does not go as planned, Molly, Gil and the Guppy Movers head out to set things right in his new home.

5.title: Batterball!
5.plot: Molly and Gil get the opportunity to see how bubble cakes are made when they step into Chef Stef's kitchen.

6.title: Temple of the Lost Puppy
6.plot: When Bubble Puppy disappears after biting an ancient magic bone, the Guppies must embark on an adventure to find him.

7.title: Space Guppies
7.plot: When the evil robot Major Bummer tries to eliminate music from the galaxy, pop Princess Molly joins forces with sci-fi versions of the Guppies to restore peace, harmony, and melody! Will they reach the Bubblestar in time?

8.title: The New Year's Dragon!
8.plot: The Guppies are excited for China's Lunar New Year Festival, where they will operate a giant festival dragon the the grand parade.

9.title: Sheep Doggy!
9.plot: When Farmer Joe's cute baby lamb wanders off the farm during a popcorn storm, Bubble Puppy becomes a sheepdog to save the day!

10.title: Bubble Baby!
10.plot: Molly's going to have a new sibling, and the Guppies are excited about babies! At the end of the day, the kids go to the hospital to meet the new baby!

11.title: Guppy Style!
11.plot: The Guppies hit the road to see a concert by Stylee, a singing sensation known for her fabulous styles! They'll travel by land, sea, and air-and encounter lots of new styles along the way-to get to the arena on time.

12.title: The Summer Camp Games
12.plot: Summer is here! Molly, Gil, and the rest of the Guppies celebrate the season with lots of outdoor fun. Gil uses his summer camping skills to rescue Bubble Puppy during the Summer Camp Games!

13.title: Trick-or-Treat, Mr. Grumpfish!
13.plot: Molly, Gil, and the rest of the Guppies are picking out costumes, trick-or-treating, and turning their classroom into a haunted house. It'll have to be really spooky if they want to scare Mr. Grumpfish.

14.title: Episode #4.14
14.plot: It's Nonny's Birthday so The Guppies want to throw a big party as they learn about it.

1.title: Call a Clambulance!
1.plot: When Oona's friend Avi breaks a bone in his tail, he needs to visit the doctor. The Bubble Guppies aren't too worried - after they learn that it's a doctor's job to make everyone feel better.

2.title: The Crayon Prix!
2.plot: Green means GO! The Bubble Guppies are learning about colors while car racing! Help them mix colors, make new shades, and speed across the finish line!

3.title: Bubble Puppy!
3.plot: Gil wants to adopt a puppy! But before he can bring the puppy home, the Bubble Guppies must learn how to take care of pets.

4.title: Build Me a Building!
4.plot: It's going to be the best doghouse EVER! But before Bubble Puppy can move into his new doggy digs, the Bubble Guppies have to build it. Help them build it while discovering all about construction.

5.title: Ducks in a Row!
5.plot: Learn about different musical instruments as you join the Bubble Guppies' marching band, and help Nonnie figure out how to lead the band when there's a duck in the way!

6.title: The Grumpfish Special!
6.plot: At the Bubble Guppies' restaurant, the group is waiting tables, cooking food,and preparing to serve their most difficult customer yet. But is there anything on the menu that can get the Grumpfish grinning?

7.title: The Moon Rocks!
7.plot: Blast off with the Bubble Guppies - it's time to learn all about the solar system! Help them begin to learn about outer space in this far-out episode.

8.title: Who's Going to Play the Big Bad Wolf?
8.plot: The play's the thing when the Bubble Guppies go to see a production of "The Three Little Pigs." But when one of the actors can't perform, it's up to Deema to put on the costume and take the stage.

9.title: We Totally Rock!
9.plot: Are you ready to rock? The Bubble Guppies are taking the stage with their guitars, drums and keyboards. Get ready to crank it up to 10 and learn about everything rock and roll.

10.title: Fishketball!
10.plot: The Bubble Guppies explore different kinds of ball games as they get ready for their big game of Fishketball! Join Team Guppies to help them practice bouncing, throwing, catching and playing together as a team.

11.title: The Legend of Pinkfoot
11.plot: The Bubble Guppies are going on a camping trip! Grab your flashlights and gather around the campfire to make smores and hear about the spooky legend of Pinkfoot!

12.title: Gup, Gup and Away!
12.plot: Pack a suitcase and hurry to the airport! Help the Bubble Guppies fly an airplane through the sky and over the clouds - just be sure to keep an eye out for airplane pirates!

13.title: The Spring Chicken is Coming!
13.plot: The Spring Chicken is about to announce the arrival of spring, but first, she needs a beautiful flower. Help the Bubble Guppies figure out how to plant and care for a flower.

14.title: Boy Meets Squirrel!
14.plot: A friendly squirrel gives Nonny an acorn that will someday grow into a tree! Join the Bubble Guppies in learning all about trees -the animals that live in them, the fruit that grows on them, and how they can help them.

15.title: Have a Cow!
15.plot: With an "oink, oink" here and a "moo, moo" there, the Bubble Guppies learn all about farm animals ... and discover that a lot of their favorite foods come from a farm too!

16.title: Super Shrimptennial Celebration!
16.plot: Jump! Leap! RelevÃ©! Bubbletucky sports fans love ballet! Molly and the rest of the Guppies want to learn how to tell a story through dance. It'll take practice, but they'll give ballet a new spin in the Super Ballet Bowl!

17.title: Happy Clam Day!
17.plot: For Clam Day, the Bubble Guppies decide to throw a party for Clam and invite his cousin Sam. But before they can send Sam an invitation, they need to learn all about how the mail works.

18.title: Can You Dig It?
18.plot: Rawrrrrrr! While the Bubble Guppies are digging for dinosaur bones, they learn all about different types of dinosaurs.

19.title: Bubble Bites!
19.plot: Glide through the aisles of the supermarket with the Bubble Guppies as they shop for fruits, vegetables and the last box of Bubble Bites for Bubble Puppy!

20.title: Haunted House Party!
20.plot: Boo! The Bubble Guppies are invited to a costume party at a haunted house! They dress up as witches, vampires, werewolves, zombies and mummies, but whoâEUR(TM)s that in the spooky ghost costume?

1.title: X Marks the Spot
1.plot: Ahoy, mateys! Set sail on a pirate adventure with Gil, Molly and their Guppy friends as they help a friendly pirate use a treasure map to find where X marks the spot!

2.title: Happy Holidays, Mr. Grumpfish!
2.plot: Everyone is getting ready for the holidays ... everyone except Mr. Grumpfish. The Guppies do their festive best to show a grumpy neighbor the joy of the holiday season.

3.title: The Lonely Rhino
3.plot: Monty is the loneliest rhinoceros in the zoo and really needs a friend. Lucky for him, Gil and the Bubble Guppies are determined to find the perfect match for Monty!

4.title: Bubble Puppy's Fin-tastic Fairy Tale
4.plot: When a Witch turns Bubble Puppy into a frog, Molly and Gil team up with famous fairytale friends to undo her mean green spell and help everyone in the Enchanted Forest live happily ever after!

5.title: The Cowgirl Parade
5.plot: Yee-haw! Molly wants to be a cowgirl like Dusty, the riden'-est, ropin'-est cowgirl in the parade! But when Dusty's calf gets into trouble, Molly has to use everything she's learned to save the day.

6.title: Firefighter Gil to the Rescue
6.plot: What happens when it's the heroic firefighters who get stuck in a tree? It's Gil and his team of Bubble Guppy firefighters to the rescue!

7.title: A Tooth on the Looth!
7.plot: Deema has a loose tooth, and when it falls out, she's going to get a visit from the Tooth Fairy! Until then, the Bubble Guppies have lots to discover about keeping a healthy smile.

8.title: Humunga-Truck!
8.plot: There are lots of different kinds of trucks, but only one that can turn into a giant robot - Humunga-Truck! The Bubble Guppies learn all about different kinds of trucks on their way to the big Truck Show!

9.title: Check It Out!
9.plot: If Molly's new friend Sandy doesn't finish her work on time, she might not be crowned Queen of the Beach at the Big Beach Ball! She needs help from some hard-working Guppies for her chance to win that crown!

10.title: The Beach Ball!
10.plot: The Bubble Brothers Circus is coming to town, and all the Guppies are getting into the act! See Goby the clown, Gil the acrobat, Oona the lion tamer ... just watch out for that pie! SPLAT!

11.title: The Sizzling Scampinis
11.plot: Goby needs help from the Bubble Guppies to retrace his steps and find his lost toy dump truck at a construction site before a wild, bucking bulldozer crushes it!

12.title: Construction Psyched
12.plot: Rawrrrrrr! While the Bubble Guppies are digging for dinosaur bones, they learn all about different types of dinosaurs.

13.title: Bubble-Cadabra
13.plot: Abracadabra! The Bubble Guppies discover magic when they stand in for a missing magician and attempt the world's greatest trick - making an elephant disappear!

14.title: Sir Nonny the Nice!
14.plot: Nonny is on a quest to become a real knight! He has a shield. He has a suit of armor. But does he have what it takes to win a knightly game of mini-golf?

15.title: Bubble Duckies!
15.plot: Welcome to the Wings Over Bubbletucky Air Show! Today the Bubble Guppies are watching a whole bunch of birds take flight! When a family of flying ducks gets lost in a storm cloud, it's up to Molly, Gil and a little duckling named Beep to rescue them!

16.title: Triple Track Train Race
16.plot: Choo choo! Ol' Number 9, an old-fashioned steam locomotive, is competing in the Triple-Track Train Race! But when a whole herd of cows wanders onto the tracks, the Bubble Guppies better think fast before it's too late!

17.title: Only the Sphinx Nose!
17.plot: Join the Bubble Guppies on an adventure to ancient Egypt, as they follow clues across the desert, along the Nile, and through a pyramid to sniff out the Sphinx's missing nose!

18.title: Bring on the Bugs!
18.plot: Jump into this underwater classroom with Molly, Gil and their fishtailed friends. Preschoolers can learn school-readiness skills like science, math, literacy and more through songs, dances, and laughs!

19.title: Good Hair Day!
19.plot: Jump into this underwater classroom with Molly, Gil and their fishtailed friends. Preschoolers can learn school-readiness skills like science, math, literacy and more through songs, dances, and laughs!

1.title: Get Ready for School!
1.plot: Oona's worried about her little friend Avi! It's his first day of school and he's nervous. From cubbies to free play, the Guppies show us the ropes and teach us that school is a great place to learn, play, and meet new friends.

2.title: The Police Cop-etition
2.plot: Stop, in the name of fun! Officer Miranda teaches Gil and the other kids how police officers use laws to keep us safe. Can the Guppies use what they've learned to earn their badges as honorary junior police officers?

3.title: The Elephant Trunk-a-Dunk!
3.plot: Gil's looking for elephants! He loves them all--African and Asian. He's in for a treat when the Guppies fill the stands for the Trunk-A-Dunk, a basketball game played by pachyderms!

4.title: Super Ballet Bowl
4.plot: Jump! Leap! RelevÃ©! Bubbletucky sports fans love ballet! Molly and the rest of the Guppies want to learn how to tell a story through dance. It'll take practice, but they'll give ballet a new spin in the Super Ballet Bowl!

5.title: The Wizard of Oz-tralia!
5.plot: After Molly and Gil meet Bobby, a nature show host from Australia, they can't wait to learn all about Australian animals. From marsupials to the amazing platypus, the Guppies can't get enough of the creatures Down Under!

6.title: The Arctic Life!
6.plot: Brrrr! The Arctic sure is cold--probably because it's filled with so many cool animals! After meeting Arctic Dan, Gil embarks on an icy expedition. With the Guppies' help, can Gil brave the elements to reach the North Pole?

7.title: Puppy Love!
7.plot: Bubble Puppy's got a cold! While Dr. Martin, the veterinarian, takes good care of him, the kids spend the day thinking about dogs--a Guppy's best friend. But will Gil's get-well card will help Bubble Puppy feel better?

8.title: The Puppy and the Ring!
8.plot: In the mythical land of Bubbledom, the evil Night Wizard has taken the magical Ring of the Sun! Someone needs to save the daytime! Will Molly and Gil return the Ring to the Sun King, or will it be nighttime in Bubbledom forever?

9.title: The Amusement Parking Lot!
9.plot: Beep beep! The Guppies love cars! But when Mr. Grouper's car breaks down on the way to an amusement park, will the kids figure out how to get this field trip rolling again?

10.title: Good Morning, Mr. Grumpfish
10.plot: The Bubble Guppies have a substitute teacher: Mr. Grumpfish. He doesn't seem to like anything! It'll take a lot for the kids to convince Mr. Grumpfish that their favorite things are worth singing about!

11.title: The Oyster Bunny!
11.plot: It's time for baby animals! Goby dreams up the Oyster Bunny, a mysterious character who loves baby animals. Can the Guppies follow an egg trail to find the elusive Oyster Bunny? A tasty treat awaits them!

12.title: The Unidentified Flying Orchestra!
12.plot: Strings! Brass! Woodwinds! Percussion! After Gil and Molly meet a conductor, the Guppies want to join an orchestra. Led by a conductor from another planet, the Guppies' orchestra will make music that's out of this world!

13.title: Come to Your Senses!
13.plot: Oh no! Nonny broke his glasses! When they're fixed, Nonny is determined to retrieve them on his own. But to do it, he'll have to depend on his other four senses to reach the glasses store before it closes!

14.title: The Bubble Bee-athalon
14.plot: Bzzzz! The Guppies are busy living the bees' life! Turning nectar into honey is tough bzzness. It takes a lot of teamwork every step of the way. Can the kids work together to make honey for the queen bee's teatime?

15.title: Party at Sea
15.plot: Anchor's away! It's time to celebrate boats with a party at sea! But when a giant ball of snow cone ice threatens to sink the party ship, can the Guppies use their nautical knowledge to save the day--and the party?

16.title: Bubble Scrubbies
16.plot: It seems like everyone in Bubbletucky is coming down with a cold--even Mr. Grouper! No need to worry; in their very own "soap opera," the Guppies will use their good hygiene to show Mr. Grouper how to get better!

17.title: Swimtastic Check-Up
17.plot: Molly and Oona run into the Mayor training for Bubbletucky's annual marathon! But when she gets a tummyache, she'll go to the hospital to get her organs checked out. She won't be able to run the big running race, but Molly, Oona, and the others will help her run her very own Mayor-thon!

24.title: A Dolphin Is a Guppy's Best Friend!
24.plot: Molly and Gil meet Buddy, a baby dolphin with the friendliest face in the sea! Today is Buddy's first birthday, and his pod is throwing him a surprise birthday party! Can the Guppies lead Buddy to the party?

26.title: Super Guppies
26.plot: When Molly and Gil bring a comic book to school, all the Guppies want to be superheroes! In the comic book's pages, the smelly villain Sid Fishy aims to make the whole city stinky! Molly and Gil dive into the adventure as Guppy Girl and Bubble Boy, but can our heroes stop Sid?

-1.title: Fruit Camp!
-1.plot: The Guppies love fruits and vegetables, but Deema doesn't want to try broccoli! When the Guppies face their scout troop initiation, Deema will have to turn over a new leaf if she wants to earn her broccoli badge.

locations: New York City, New York, USA
imdb.title: Bubble Guppies
plot: The adventures of six fish-tailed kids- Molly, Gil, Oona, Deema, Nonny, and Goby.::Jakeylon Teal
